WEBVTT

00:07.215 --> 00:10.093
McQUEEN: So you're going to give a speech
or a toast or something?

00:10.176 --> 00:11.386
What? When?

00:11.469 --> 00:14.681
At your sister's wedding?
Come on, we're only a few days away.

00:14.764 --> 00:17.350
Speech? That makes me kind of nervous.

00:17.434 --> 00:19.936
You know, I ain't much for
getting up in front of folks.

00:20.020 --> 00:23.356
Ah, Mater, I have complete faith
that you can... (GASPS) Huh?

00:26.776 --> 00:28.069
Looky that.

00:28.153 --> 00:29.946
-"Brakelight Pictures"?
-CAR 1: Quiet on the set.

00:30.030 --> 00:31.364
-BELLA: Camera rolling.
-(BOTH GASP)

00:31.448 --> 00:32.866
And action!

00:33.616 --> 00:35.452
(ROARING AND SPUTTERING)

00:38.580 --> 00:40.081
(GRUNTING)

00:41.916 --> 00:44.044
-Cut!
-CAR 2: Reset! Back to one!

00:44.127 --> 00:45.795
Oh, this is so cool.

00:45.879 --> 00:48.381
Are you...
You're Lightning McQueen, aren't you?

00:48.465 --> 00:50.050
(CHUCKLES) Yes, I am.

00:50.133 --> 00:53.386
-And this is my friend, Mater...
-Bell! It's Lightning McQueen.

00:53.470 --> 00:55.513
We have got to find a part for him.

00:56.056 --> 00:58.016
Are you serious? Me?

00:58.099 --> 00:59.309
In a movie?

01:00.143 --> 01:03.855
<i>Hitting the highway, a couple of friends</i>

01:03.938 --> 01:08.026
<i>With new adventures 'round every bend</i>

01:08.109 --> 01:12.072
<i>Whether racing fast or getting towed</i>

01:12.155 --> 01:16.284
<i>We're ever together, cars on the road</i>

01:17.952 --> 01:19.662
(EERIE MUSIC PLAYING)

01:22.248 --> 01:24.292
Whoa-ho! Look at this.

01:24.375 --> 01:26.377
Oh, oh, Mater, you know who that is,
don't you?

01:26.461 --> 01:27.462
Uh...

01:27.545 --> 01:31.091
McQUEEN: That's legendary
horror director Bella Cadavre.

01:31.174 --> 01:33.218
Oh, yeah. Of course it is.

01:33.301 --> 01:37.472
Now the thing about her, she insists
on using only practical effects.

01:37.555 --> 01:39.390
You know, real rubber monsters.

01:39.474 --> 01:41.726
There's none of that fakey CGI stuff.

01:41.810 --> 01:43.144
What's CGI?

01:43.228 --> 01:45.188
Well, Mater, that's technical.

01:45.271 --> 01:48.274
It comes out of a computer, somehow.

01:48.733 --> 01:50.318
Lightning McQueen, huh?

01:50.401 --> 01:52.362
Hey, let's cast him as Deputy Hazard.

01:52.445 --> 01:54.322
Ugh. Yes, please.

01:54.405 --> 01:57.075
The kid playing the deputy
is busting my chops.

01:57.158 --> 02:00.078
Go ahead, swap in
the celebrity guest star.

02:00.161 --> 02:01.830
(LAUGHS) It's going to be great.

02:01.913 --> 02:05.333
Oh, excuse me, I don't want
to take anybody's job.

02:05.416 --> 02:08.169
-Too late. The other guy's out.
-Gone. Dead to us.

02:08.253 --> 02:11.965
-Uh... Okay.
-Go, get 'em, buddy! Ha-ha!

02:17.262 --> 02:18.555
Do I have a script?

02:18.638 --> 02:20.056
Oh, don't worry. It's one line.

02:20.140 --> 02:22.725
-Huh. One line?
-Les, could you read him the line?

02:22.809 --> 02:24.602
(SIGHS) Don't look at me.

02:24.978 --> 02:27.605
Okay, uh, but what's the line?

02:27.689 --> 02:30.400
The line is "Don't look at me."

02:30.483 --> 02:33.319
Oh, uh... Well, what if it was
something more like...

02:33.403 --> 02:36.072
The line is "Don't look at me."

02:36.865 --> 02:39.325
Oh, Lightning,
you're doing great. (LAUGHS)

02:39.409 --> 02:40.827
You need to wait outside.

02:40.910 --> 02:41.911
(BELL RINGS)

02:41.995 --> 02:45.373
<i>Attack of the Space Zombies from Planet B.</i>
Scene 10 Charlie, Take one.

02:45.748 --> 02:46.749
BELLA: Action!

02:47.250 --> 02:51.296
It's like all his innards were
completely gelatinized.

02:51.880 --> 02:52.922
But how?

02:53.548 --> 02:55.258
-Ahem.
-Oh. (STAMMERS)

02:55.341 --> 02:57.719
-Don't LOOK at me.
-BELLA: Ugh! Cut!

02:58.052 --> 03:00.430
"Me." It's "me." "Don't look at me."

03:00.638 --> 03:02.098
Okay? All right?

03:02.223 --> 03:03.641
Ah, okay. Now I got it.

03:03.725 --> 03:05.643
<i>Attack of the Space Zombies from Planet B.</i>

03:05.727 --> 03:07.103
Scene 10 Charlie, take two.

03:07.187 --> 03:08.188
BELLA: Action.

03:08.563 --> 03:09.772
DON'T look at me.

03:10.023 --> 03:11.399
-Cut!
-Take three.

03:12.108 --> 03:13.943
-Don't look at ME!
-BELLA: Cut!

03:14.027 --> 03:15.028
Take four.

03:15.111 --> 03:16.321
Don't look AT me.

03:16.404 --> 03:17.530
Cut, cut, cut!

03:18.114 --> 03:20.366
Take 37.

03:21.451 --> 03:22.660
Don't look at me.

03:23.286 --> 03:24.871
Close enough! Keep rolling.

03:28.625 --> 03:30.835
(SCREAMS) That's cold! Sorry.

03:30.919 --> 03:31.961
BELLA: Do it again.

03:32.212 --> 03:33.630
-(SCREAMS)
-Again!

03:33.713 --> 03:34.714
-Ugh!
-BELLA: Again!

03:34.839 --> 03:35.840
BELLA: Again!

03:39.886 --> 03:41.554
Can you look more surprised?

03:41.971 --> 03:43.264
(SIGHS WEARILY)

03:45.642 --> 03:46.643
(SLURPING)

03:47.518 --> 03:48.561
(SIGHS)

03:48.853 --> 03:50.772
Aw, it's okay, buddy.

03:50.855 --> 03:53.942
Oh, hey, look. I'm from planet Zip-Zorp.

03:54.025 --> 03:56.277
-(CHUCKLING)
-(SPUTTERING)

03:58.488 --> 04:00.823
Hmm. How about that guy?

04:00.907 --> 04:01.908
It's your call.

04:01.991 --> 04:03.743
Listen, I'm willing to try anything.

04:05.328 --> 04:06.329
-Excuse me.
-Uh-oh.

04:06.829 --> 04:09.666
Can you play a lovable, scared
and confused ne'er do well?

04:09.749 --> 04:11.918
-Who, me?
-Are you funny?

04:12.001 --> 04:14.462
You mean funny ha ha, or funny weird?

04:15.213 --> 04:16.881
I think you got this.

04:17.590 --> 04:19.342
(EERIE MUSIC PLAYING)

04:19.425 --> 04:22.095
Are you sure about what you saw?

04:22.679 --> 04:26.766
Whatever it was,
it looked right through me.

04:27.725 --> 04:29.811
Hey, what if it was written more like,

04:29.894 --> 04:33.523
"It was a brain on wheels,
with a mouth full of yellow chompers.

04:33.606 --> 04:36.609
"I mean, what am I going to do,
ask for its ID?"

04:36.693 --> 04:38.528
-(ALL LAUGHING)
-That's better.

04:38.861 --> 04:41.906
Where you been all my life,
Mr. Yuck It Up Tow Truck?

04:42.907 --> 04:44.450
Ooh. Hey. Wow.

04:44.534 --> 04:47.662
So, you seem to really be
giving them what they want.

04:47.745 --> 04:48.913
Seems like it.

04:49.789 --> 04:52.709
MATER: Huh. Let's see here.
Here's a good one.

04:53.167 --> 04:54.210
-Boo!
-(GASPS)

04:54.794 --> 04:55.795
Rawr!

04:55.878 --> 04:57.213
Oh, look, there he is.

04:57.297 --> 04:58.464
We have a new part for you.

04:58.548 --> 05:00.341
The wisecracking scientist.

05:00.425 --> 05:02.760
Oh, thank goodness,
because I was just going to...

05:02.844 --> 05:05.054
Anyone can play that goofy ne'er do well.

05:05.138 --> 05:07.140
This part has some juice.

05:07.223 --> 05:09.642
It needs your special touch.

05:10.977 --> 05:13.604
The lights are
coming from the cemetery tonight.

05:13.688 --> 05:16.482
What do we even know about these things?

05:18.609 --> 05:22.613
You just give me five minutes
with this undead hunk of bad news,

05:23.072 --> 05:25.616
I'll tell you what it had for lunch
last Tuesday.

05:25.700 --> 05:28.286
-(ALL LAUGHING)
-BELLA: I told you this guy's money.

05:28.494 --> 05:29.912
Oh, come on.

05:30.955 --> 05:33.458
BELLA: You're a hidden talent.
Let it blossom!

05:33.541 --> 05:35.543
-Huh?
-BELLA: Look, you can do anything.

05:35.626 --> 05:36.836
What is all this?

05:36.919 --> 05:38.254
Why am I all in blue?

05:38.338 --> 05:40.923
That wacky scientist bit?
(BLOWS RASPBERRY) That's old news.

05:41.007 --> 05:44.469
We need you for the role of the president.

05:46.429 --> 05:48.973
Who, me? The president?

05:49.057 --> 05:51.809
And we'd like you
to write your own speech.

05:52.393 --> 05:53.394
(SCOFFS)

05:53.811 --> 05:55.855
Whoa, the president.

05:59.650 --> 06:01.361
(TV PLAYING)

06:03.112 --> 06:06.532
(GROANS) Come on. Why can't I do this?

06:06.616 --> 06:08.576
Why are you so wound up anyway?

06:08.659 --> 06:10.953
I'm trying to think
up my president's speech.

06:11.079 --> 06:12.288
Mater, I got to be honest.

06:12.372 --> 06:14.791
I always thought I'd be the one
who'd be good at this.

06:14.874 --> 06:15.875
What am I missing?

06:16.918 --> 06:19.045
Lightning, you're good at everything.

06:19.796 --> 06:23.132
You've got to leave a few leftovers
for the rest of us.

06:24.342 --> 06:27.845
Besides, you're crushing it
as the scatterbrained deputy.

06:27.929 --> 06:30.973
Yeah. I don't think he's meant
to be scatterbrained.

06:31.557 --> 06:32.725
Ooh. Sorry.

06:39.357 --> 06:41.317
Hey, look, I've been a jerk.

06:41.734 --> 06:43.778
I'll try to be a better
friend today, all right?

06:44.195 --> 06:46.781
Aw, I never doubted you, buddy.

06:51.035 --> 06:52.495
BOTH: Whoa!

06:52.578 --> 06:54.288
-McQUEEN: What is that?
-Dadgum.

06:54.372 --> 06:56.582
What's going on? It's all different.

06:56.666 --> 06:57.917
Uh, excuse me.

06:58.000 --> 06:59.335
And you are?

06:59.585 --> 07:01.045
I'm Deputy Hazard.

07:01.129 --> 07:03.840
The soft-spoken lawman
who lives by the code of the badge.

07:03.923 --> 07:07.260
And I'm the President
of the United States.

07:07.343 --> 07:08.928
(CHUCKLES) Oh, you guys.

07:09.011 --> 07:10.012
Uh-huh.

07:10.096 --> 07:13.224
This show is taking a new direction.
Total rewrite.

07:13.724 --> 07:16.102
Anyway, drop your costumes
over at wardrobe

07:16.185 --> 07:17.687
and, uh, good luck out there.

07:18.312 --> 07:21.315
-(SCOFFS) What?
-Ain't that a kick in the tires.

07:21.399 --> 07:24.652
-(TOOTS) Mater? Lightning!
-Ivy, what are you doing here?

07:24.735 --> 07:27.613
-Ivy! Look at you.
-What about the circus?

07:27.697 --> 07:28.948
Oh, the circus was amazing.

07:29.031 --> 07:31.868
But what are the chances
I get discovered on stage

07:31.951 --> 07:35.455
and cast in a real movie?
Once in a lifetime, right?

07:35.538 --> 07:37.373
Yeah, that never happens.

07:37.540 --> 07:39.500
So, what? No more zombie horror?

07:39.584 --> 07:41.836
(SCOFFS) Heard that movie
was a trainwreck.

07:42.128 --> 07:43.546
Now it's a musical.

07:43.754 --> 07:44.922
Huh, you don't say.

07:45.339 --> 07:46.841
So, what's with the funny outfits?

07:46.924 --> 07:47.925
-Nothing.
-No reason.

07:48.009 --> 07:49.260
-CAR: And roll playback.
-Ooh. Ooh!

07:49.427 --> 07:50.845
They're ready for me on set.

07:50.928 --> 07:52.805
I got to go. It was great seeing you guys.

07:53.222 --> 07:54.223
Wish me luck.

07:55.016 --> 07:56.684
And action!

07:57.018 --> 08:00.146
(SINGING) <i>I'm just a brain on wheels</i>
<i>with a mouthful of chompers</i>

08:00.271 --> 08:02.607
<i>Chomp, chomp, chomp, chomp</i>
<i>chompity-chomp chompers</i>

08:02.690 --> 08:05.067
<i>We'll make you swoon</i>
<i>In your cocoon</i>

08:05.151 --> 08:09.071
<i>It's a dancing invasion</i>
<i>Of super amazin' zombie alien cars</i>

08:09.155 --> 08:13.451
<i>Yeah</i>
<i>And that's who we are</i>

08:13.910 --> 08:16.162
Well, so go our acting careers.

08:16.245 --> 08:18.789
You know, Mater,
I never got to hear your speech.

08:18.873 --> 08:21.459
-Speech? What speech?
-Your president's speech.

08:21.542 --> 08:22.627
Oh, yeah, well...

08:22.710 --> 08:24.253
-Uh...
-And action.

08:24.337 --> 08:26.672
(CLEARS THROAT) As your president,

08:26.756 --> 08:29.175
I call upon the cars of the world

08:29.258 --> 08:33.179
to rise up against this
zombie alien invasion

08:33.304 --> 08:36.933
and to squelch this brainy-headed scourge.

08:37.016 --> 08:41.687
Or else, it's only a matter of time
before they blow up the Earth!

08:41.771 --> 08:42.980
McQUEEN: Mater, that was great.

08:43.064 --> 08:45.483
-Is that it?
-Shoot, I'm just getting started.
